<title><![CDATA[ Daily Flash – April 26, 2026]]></title>
<description><![CDATA[A federal jury just slapped Carnival with $300,000 after ruling they served a passenger 14 drinks in nine hours—and she wound up face-planting down the stairs. Now everyone’s questioning drink packages, wristband trackers and who’s really to blame when you’re three sheets to the wind on deck. Here’s why this verdict could turn your next vacation into a hyper-monitored booze cruise. ]]></description>
